Here is a concise C++ program to read a text file line by line and count the occurrences of a specific word:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>
using namespace std;

int main() {
  ifstream file("file.txt");
  string line;
  int count = 0;
  string word = "hello";

  while (getline(file, line)) {
    int pos = 0;
    while ((pos = line.find(word, pos)) != string::npos) {
      count++;
      pos += word.length();
    }
  }

  cout << "The word " << word << " appears " << count << " times.";
}
```

The key points are:

- Include the necessary header files (iostream, fstream, string)
- Open the text file with an ifstream 
- Read each line using getline into a string variable
- Use find() to search for the word in each line 
- Increment a counter when the word is found
- After the loop, print out the final count

